aaos (0.1.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Architecture: both orchestration modes (plan/decompose and
    persistent/direct) now route through the unified PlanExecutor.
    The Bootstrap persistent agent is no longer used for per-submit
    goals.
  * Each subtask now runs as a full multi-turn agent. Iteration budget
    is set by role.orchestration.max_iterations (default 50) instead
    of the old retry.max_attempts+10 formula (default ~12).
  * Bug 9 closed: fallback_generalist_plan deleted. A malformed Planner
    response now propagates as a correctable error through the replan
    loop; after max_replans exhausted the run fails cleanly with no
    hallucinated report on disk.
  * New role YAML fields: orchestration.max_iterations (u32, default 50)
    and require_declared_output (bool, default false). fetcher role sets
    require_declared_output: true.
  * New SubtaskOutputMissing advisory audit event when a subtask finishes
    without writing its declared output and require_declared_output is
    false.
  * Classifier output changed from plan/persistent to decompose/direct;
    fallback on LLM error is now direct (was plan). Wire API preserved.

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Fri, 24 Apr 2026 22:00:00 +0000

aaos (0.0.5-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Feature: agentd submit now auto-classifies the goal and routes
    it to plan mode (Planner + PlanExecutor DAG) or persistent mode
    (Bootstrap persistent agent) automatically.  A cheap single-shot
    LLM call inspects the goal text before any agent work begins.
    Operators can force a mode with --orchestration [plan|persistent];
    the classifier is bypassed.  Surfaces which mode was picked via
    a structured audit event and a journald log line.
  * Previously a missing role catalog silently fell through to the
    Bootstrap path; plan mode now errors cleanly with a pointer
    at journalctl.

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Fri, 24 Apr 2026 20:30:00 +0000

aaos (0.0.4-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix: grep tool now routes daemon-side under the namespaced
    backend.  grep shells out to `rg` (ripgrep); the worker's
    seccomp kill-filter denies execve, so every grep call under
    confinement failed with "failed to spawn rg: Operation not
    permitted".  Surfaced by the v0.0.3 self-reflection droplet
    run (Bug 8).

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Fri, 24 Apr 2026 17:00:00 +0000

aaos (0.0.3-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix: memory_store / memory_query / memory_delete now route
    daemon-side under confinement.  Previously these tools were
    missing from both WORKER_SIDE_TOOLS and DAEMON_SIDE_TOOLS, so
    under the namespaced backend they failed with
    `tool error: tool memory_X not available in worker`.  Surfaced
    by the v0.0.2 extended QA pass (Bug 7).

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Fri, 24 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0000

aaos (0.0.2-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix: `.deb` now includes `--features namespaced-agents`. v0.0.1
    shipped without it, so AAOS_DEFAULT_BACKEND=namespaced silently
    fell back to InProcessBackend — confinement disabled.
  * Fix: `agentd submit` now prints the daemon's error message on
    failed runs (e.g. bad API key) instead of silent
    `failed (0k in / 0k out, 0s)`.
  * Fix: MCP client + server now log startup status. Prior versions
    left operators with zero visibility into MCP state.
  * Fix: NamespacedBackend::stop now reaps child processes. Prior
    versions left a `[aaos-agent-worker] <defunct>` zombie per run.
  * Fix: "using NamespacedBackend" startup log fires once per process,
    not twice.
  * Packaging: `debian/copyright` references common-licenses instead
    of inlining Apache-2.0; systemd unit moved to usr/lib/systemd/
    per Debian Trixie merged-usr; release binaries stripped to reduce
    package size.

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 22:00:00 +0000

aaos (0.0.1-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * First tagged .deb release.  CI-built on v* tag push via
    .github/workflows/release.yml; builds inside a debian:13 container so
    cargo-deb encodes Debian's libc/systemd minimums.
  * Agentic-by-default .deb surface: --features mcp enabled by default;
    21 AgentSkills bundled under /usr/share/aaos/skills/; postinst
    probes Landlock + unprivileged userns and generates
    /etc/default/aaos.example; new `agentd configure` subcommand for
    one-step API key setup; /etc/aaos/mcp-servers.yaml.example template.
  * Clippy gate flipped to -D warnings after fixing 57 latent lints.

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Sat, 19 Apr 2026 19:00:00 +0000

aaos (0.0.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * No installable artifact — this stanza records the pre-v0.0.1
    development history in dpkg-changelog form.  See CHANGELOG.md at
    the repo root for the full human-readable record.
  * Runtime foundation: capability-based security, two-level tool
    enforcement, AgentServices + Tool traits, LLM execution loop, MCP
    message routing, human-in-the-loop approval.
  * Persistent agents + request-response IPC; managed context windows
    with transparent summarization; episodic memory store with cosine
    similarity over embeddings.
  * Self-bootstrapping swarm (Docker PID 1 + Bootstrap Agent).
  * Multi-provider LLM (DeepSeek, Anthropic, OpenAI-compatible);
    per-agent token budgets; semaphore-bounded inference scheduler.
  * Computed orchestration: Planner + deterministic PlanExecutor DAG
    walk; role catalog at /etc/aaos/roles/; four bundled roles.
  * Agent-kernel primitives: reasoning-slot scheduler; per-task TTL +
    latency tracking; dynamic model routing via role.model_ladder +
    escalation signals; runtime-side tool confinement on
    NamespacedBackend (Landlock + seccomp + user/mount/pid namespaces).
  * Bidirectional MCP integration (aaos-mcp crate, --features mcp).
  * Operator CLI (submit/list/status/stop/logs/roles) + NDJSON
    streaming + BroadcastAuditLog + agentd(1) man page + aaos
    system group.
  * Debian packaging (2026-04-15, commits 5717906 + 8d45691): .deb
    buildable via cargo-deb; postinst creates aaos user + group;
    systemd StateDirectory/RuntimeDirectory own dir creation; socket
    at /run/agentd/agentd.sock mode 0660; purge cleans state + user.

 -- Jounes <jounes.ds@gmail.com>  Sat, 29 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
